                     <interp inst="t18290910-278-person2613" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I never said any such word - when I took him I said, "It is you, Sir, is it?" for he had been attempting to take the beads off my child's neck two days before - this was about ten o'clock in the evening; as we walked we were abreast - there was no one but the child, the prisoner, and myself, in a line; I saw it taken, and collared him directly.</p>
